![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/5f5033df-154e-4fe7-bc38-f754ef5ea0a2/223.jpg?format=original)

Moon Knight is out! The series on Disney+ just made its debut and to celebrate we are talking the Jeff Lemire/Greg Smallwood run of Moon Knight from 2016! Not only is the story an instant classic with amazing visuals, themes around mental health, and bat sh\*t implications, but it gives us an intimate look into the Rubix Cube of the man named Marc Spector. Join us as we review one of Lemire's best works while getting ourselves ready for the madness that will be the Moon Knight TV Series!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

  
